===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|néologisme|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|sc=polytonic|νέος||new|lang=grc}} + {{term|sc=polytonic|λόγος||tr=logos|word|lang=grc}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{context|linguistics|lang=en}} A word or phrase which has recently been coined; a new word or phrase.
# {{context|linguistics|uncountable|lang=en}} The act or instance of coining, or uttering a new word.
# {{context|psychiatry|lang=en}} The newly coined, meaningless words or phrases of someone with a [[psychosis]], usually [[schizophrenia]].

====Usage notes====
For a word to be no longer considered new, it needs to be understood by a significant portion of the population as having always been a valid word. For that to occur the word must have been in common use for approximately one generation &mdash; fifteen to twenty years &mdash; but there is no universally accepted measure.

